pgmap - PostgreSQL-backed generic key-value store for Go

  go get github.com/xtdlib/pgmap

Usage:

  m := pgmap.New[string, string]("my-table")
  m.Set("key", "value")
  v := m.Get("key")

Options:

  pgmap.DSN("postgres://...")    custom connection string
  pgmap.SyncCommit()             enable WAL flush (default: async)
  pgmap.Unlogged()               unlogged table (fast, no crash safety)
  pgmap.MinConns(n)              minimum idle pool connections (default: 3)

Auto-detects unix sockets before falling back to TCP.

Operations:

  Set, Get, GetOr, Has, Delete, Clear, Purge
  SetNX (set if not exists)
  SetNZ (set if non-zero)
  Update (atomic read-modify-write)
  AddRat (atomic rational number addition)
  WithLock (table-level locking with transactions)
  Keys, KeysBackward, All, KeysWhere, AllWhere, Map

Every operation has a Try* variant that returns errors instead of panicking.

Type mapping:

  string          -> TEXT
  int, uint, etc  -> BIGINT
  float32/64      -> DOUBLE PRECISION
  bool            -> BOOLEAN
  []byte          -> BYTEA
  time.Time       -> BIGINT (UnixNano)
  Scanner+Stringer-> TEXT
  everything else -> JSON

Requires Go 1.24+, PostgreSQL.
